#meta-data title: Signatures

## Signatures

### Create Signature

<div class="api-content">

<div class="table-content no-scrollbar">

#### Headers

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
                <td style="text-align:left">Authorization
                  <div class="table-description">string</div>
                </td>
                <td style="text-align:left">Set value to <code>Bearer SECRET_KEY</code></td>
              </tr><tr>
                  <td style="text-align:left">Accept
                    <div class="table-description">string</div>
                  </td>
                  <td style="text-align:left"><code>application/json</code></td>
                </tr>  </tbody>
</table>

#### Body params

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">name
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">The name of the signature
            </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">signature
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">This is a base64 string
            </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">documents
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">The documents the signature should appear on. Can be any of invoice, receipts, deposit_receipts, payslip, bill, quote, paid_expenses
            </td>
        </tr></tbody>
</table>

<div class="optional-parameters">

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">position
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">The position of signature
            </td>
        </tr></tbody>
</table>

</div>

### Get Signatures

<div class="api-content">

<div class="table-content no-scrollbar">

#### Headers

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
                <td style="text-align:left">Authorization
                  <div class="table-description">string</div>
                </td>
                <td style="text-align:left">Set value to <code>Bearer SECRET_KEY</code></td>
              </tr>  </tbody>
</table>

</div>

<div class="code-content">

```js
const axios = require("axios");

axios({
  method: "GET",
  url: "/api/v3/signatures",
  headers: {
    Authorization: "Bearer {{token}}",
  },
})
  .then((response) => console.log(response.data))
  .catch((error) => console.error(error));
```

```go
package main

import (
    "bytes"
    "fmt"
    "io/ioutil"
    "net/http"
)

func main() {
    client := &http.Client{}

    req, err := http.NewRequest("GET", "/api/v3/signatures", nil)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    req.Header = map[string][]string{
        "Authorization": {"Bearer {{token}}"}
    }
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    body, err := ioutil.ReadAll(resp.Body)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Println(err)
        return
    }
    fmt.Println(string(body))
}
```

### Update Signature

<div class="api-content">

<div class="table-content no-scrollbar">

#### Headers

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
                <td style="text-align:left">Authorization
                  <div class="table-description">string</div>
                </td>
                <td style="text-align:left">Set value to <code>Bearer SECRET_KEY</code></td>
              </tr><tr>
                  <td style="text-align:left">Accept
                    <div class="table-description">string</div>
                  </td>
                  <td style="text-align:left"><code>application/json</code></td>
                </tr>  </tbody>
</table>

#### Body params

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">name
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">The name of the signature
            </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">signature
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">This is a base64 string
            </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">documents
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">The documents the signature should appear on. Can be any of invoice, receipts, deposit_receipts, payslip, bill, quote, paid_expenses
            </td>
        </tr></tbody>
</table>

<div class="optional-parameters">

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">position
            <div class="table-description">string</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">The position of signature
            </td>
        </tr></tbody>
</table>

</div>

#### Path Parameters

<table>
  <tbody>
<tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">id
            <div class="table-description">integer</div>
          </td>
          <td style="text-align:left">The id of the signature to update
            </td>
        </tr></tbody>
</table>

</div>

<div class="code-content">

```js
const axios = require("axios");

axios({
  method: "POST",
  url: "/api/v3/signatures/:id",
  headers: {
    Accept: "application/json",
    Authorization: "Bearer {{token}}",
  },

  data: {
```
